-- Spanish 10-Year Bond Yield Advances to Euro-Era Record of 7.08%
-- B y   L u c y   M e a k i n
-- 2012-06-18T08:10:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-18/spanish-10-year-bond-yield-advances-to-euro-era-record-of-7-08-.html
Spanish 10-year bonds extended a
decline, pushing the yield on the securities 20 basis points
higher to 7.08 percent at 9:08 a.m. London time, a  euro-era
record .  The extra yield investors demand to hold the securities
over similar-maturity German bunds expanded to 562 basis points,
or 5.62 percentage points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucy Meakin in London at 
